# WF-012 (2026-05-20): do not mark checked-in artifact fixtures as Git LFS.
# This repository currently has zero LFS pointer files, while thousands of
# historical artifact parquet/xlsx files are committed as normal Git blobs.
# The stale filter caused every checkout to emit
# "Encountered <N> files that should have been pointers, but weren't", and
# GitHub Copilot Code Review failed with stderr maxBuffer overflow while
# checking out PR branches. Keep artifact uploads in Actions artifacts, not
# repo-level LFS attributes, unless a future migration converts the files into
# real LFS pointers in the same commit.
